OL,6,FDefence lawyer Marion Weir asked for
OL,7,Fthe case to be adjourned for the
OL,8,Fpreparation of a probation service pre-
OL,9,Fsentence report.
OL,11,FThis was, she said, to provide the
OL,12,Fcourt with full background information
OL,13,Fabout Teasdale and his offending, and
OL,14,Falso a brain injury from which he was
OL,15,Fsuffering.
OL,17,FJudge Michael Fanning agreed and
OL,18,Fadjourned the case, saying that no
OL,19,Fsentencing options, including a
OL,20,Fcustodial term, were being ruled out.
